rf

Class Utility

  • java.lang.Object
    • rf.Utility

  • public class Utility
extends java.lang.Object
    This is a Utility class for all RF methods and provides methods to normalize descriptors to calculate mean, variance and standard deviation and so on.
    Author:
    Chris Wendler

    • Method Detail

      • normalizeDescriptors

        public static void normalizeDescriptors(java.util.List<ImageContainer> database,
                        DescriptorType descriptorOfInterest,
                        Utility.Normalization type)
        Normalizes the descriptors of given type and given database.
        Parameters:
        database - is an image list containing.
        descriptorOfInterest - denotes for which descriptortype the operation is applied.
        type - denotes the type of normalization: GAUSSIAN: apply gaussian normalization by dividing each component of the corresponding descriptor by 3 times the standard deviation. GAUSSIAN_0to1: the same as GAUSSIAN except that the values are normalized to the interval [0,1]. JUSTUS: normalizes the descriptors by dividing each entry by the corresponding variance. IDF: denotes the inverse document frequency normalization for images.
